				<div class="tab-pane active" id="description">
					<p>Creation of a more dynamic workplace where new ways of working have been implemented to promote practices such as &laquo;desk sharing&raquo;, home working, result orientation and more flexible ways in which teams are structured and are working. Within the Federal Public Service Social Security (FPS SS) the employees are organisers of their own life. They are not told anymore when, where and how they have to work. Only results are evaluated. Our business objective was to become a sexy and sustainable federal public service in order to achieve three main HR challenges: to find talented people, to retain the right people and to make our people happy.</p>

					<h4>Why the innovation was developed</h4>
					<p>The FPS Social Security needs to attract motivated and talented staff and offer a pleasant work climate. In 2005 the FPS Social Security faced a new challenge: how to find and retain the staff it needed. The gap between the number of people leaving the labour market and the young ones entering it will get bigger by 2020.vPreviously, we could convince with job security and a state pension. Nowadays, many young people choose rather an employer than a job. Retaining of current employees and recruitment of new staff were the main reasons for introducing this project in our organisation. </p>
					<h4>Objectives</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Changing our organisation culture through value driven people management and a result oriented approach</li>
						<li>Digitalizing our work processes and encouraging E-working</li>
						<li>Implementing a dynamic office where no one has his own desk and where the well-being of our people comes first  </li>
						<li>Studying the satisfaction of our clients and improving our global accessibility</li>
						<li>Guiding our people in this change process and applying a transparent and open communication policy</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Main beneficiaries</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Our own staff (+/- 1200 employees)
						<li>Our B2B partners
						<li>Our clients (e.g. people with a handicap, local social workers, &hellip;) benefitting from higher productivity and efficiency of the FPS SS
					</ul>

					<h4>Existing similar practices</h4>
					<p>Telework already exists in several federal public services. Some are also experimenting new ways of working like culture shift, dynamic office, no time clock.</p>

				</div>
