					<h4>Efficiency</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>30% reduction in office space saves federal government 6 million Euros each year
						<li>A 55% reduction in the use of paper for printing
						<li>An 88% reduction in the number of printers: from 450 to 50
						<li>A 60% reduction in office furniture expenditure
						<li>A 22% reduction of paper-based archives and documents
					</ul>
					<h4>Effectiveness</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Bi-annual 180 degree evaluation of all mangers by their subordinates with approx. 50% of employees participating in the evaluation</li>
						<li>Coaching of 50 managers to improve their leadership competences</li>
					</ul>
					<h4>Service quality</h4>
					<p><strong>Responsiveness: </strong>Productivity increased e.g. faster decisions by more than 20% on interventions concerning people with a handicap</p>
					<h4>Other improvements</h4>
					<p>Improved employee satisfaction:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Young graduates opt more for our organisation within the federal administration: from rank 10 in 2005 to top 3 in 2009 </li>
						<li>Lower turnover rate: 4.36% in 2008 and 4.77% in 2009 (federal average = 10.7%)</li>
						<li>Lower absence rate (5.47% in 2009) in comparison to federal average (5.67%)</li>
						<li>Satisfaction rate is 88%</li>
						<li>Benchmark to 14 federal institutions, our people are most happy</li>
					</ul>

				</div>
				<div class="tab-pane" id="implementation">
					<h4>Testing</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>2007: Test of the dynamic office concept and stop of time clock, 45 persons from 3 different services </li>
						<li>2005-2007: Board members and some staff members (60 in total) are using teleworking</li>
						<li>Creation of five so called NoVoTeams  to implement the new strategy</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Implementation</h4>
					<p><strong>Tools used: </strong></p>
					<p>The 5 NoVo programs were implemented respectively treating the aspects of :</p>
					<ul>
						<li>HR and culture</li>
						<li>Dynamic office</li>
						<li>Digitalising</li>
						<li>Client orientation</li>
						<li>Communication and change management</li>
					</ul>
					<p><strong>Resources used: </strong></p>
					<ul>
						<li>Total investment of EUR 10 million, including all costs of the implementation of the new program. </li>
						<li>11 FTE during three years responsible for implementation of the project. </li>
						<li>Around 200 staff were supporting the implementation through workshops and volunteering</li>
						<li>Several consultants helped with specific inputs such as interior design,  architecture and the culture survey</li>
						<li>The lump sum investment of EUR 10 million was offset after 1.5 years by the saving of EUR 6 million per annum through reduction in office spaces.</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Diffusion</h4>
					<p></p>
					<p>Implement time: 3 years</p>
					<h4>Partnerships</h4>
					<p>Public Sector:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Office for Real Estate of the public service: supporting role in elaboration of dynamic office concept</li>
						<li>General Kingdom Archives: supporting role in project document management, took over valuable archives from us </li>
						<li>FPS Personnel &amp; Organisation: support for result oriented aspect, as for proposing tools for realisation of surveys with accompanying analyses.</li>
					</ul>
					<p>Private Sector:</p>

					<p>Several consultants were associated for the change process, but the input of consultants remained limited (e.g. interior design and architecture, culture survey&hellip;)

					</p>

